theorem Topology.interiorClosure_iter6_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure A)))))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  -- Apply the 5-fold idempotence lemma to `interior (closure A)`.
  have h :=
    Topology.interiorClosure_iter5_idempotent
      (A := interior (closure (A : Set X)))
  -- Simplify the right-hand side using basic idempotence.
  simpa [Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent (A := A)] using h

theorem Topology.closureInteriorClosure_eq_closure_of_isOpen_set
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- First inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    exact
      closure_mono
        (interior_subset :
          (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
  -- Second inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    -- Since `A` is open, it sits inside `interior (closure A)`.
    have hSub :
        (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X)) hA
    exact closure_mono hSub
  -- Conclude equality of the two closures.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂
